-- Fed to keep holdings steady near $2 trillion
-- 
-- Tue Aug 10, 2010 3:42pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/08/10/us-usa-fed-purchases-idUSTRE6794N820100810

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The Federal Reserve said on Tuesday it will to keep its holdings of domestic securities steady at around $2.054 trillion with purchases of Treasuries beginning August 17. 

 The Fed said in a statement that it will focus its purchases in the 2- to 10-year range of Treasury securities, but also said it could buy a broader range of Treasuries including inflation protected securities. (Reporting by  Mark Felsenthal )